content.html:
I made time to get over to Sauvie Island (aka Wappatoo Island) to shoot some this past weekend.  It’s a beautiful spot where the Willamette River meets the great Columbia River.  Dragged the ol’ view camera out too.  Hopefully, a few will turn out.

content.value:
I made time to get over to Sauvie Island (aka Wappatoo Island) to shoot some this past weekend.  It’s a beautiful spot where the Willamette River meets the great Columbia River.  Dragged the ol’ view camera out too.  Hopefully, a few will turn out.
 
 A dirt road leading into long thin trees covered with moss. 
 
 
 A blue channel of water cutting through green grass and yellowed reeds with a river and clouds beyond it. 
 
 
 Blackberry bushes in the foreground with the Columbia River beyond it under a blue sky with fluffy white clouds.
